: Bristol, Rhode Island Bristol, incorporated 1680 and included the former locations of Sowams and Montaup Mount Hope, which were Massasoit's and King Philip's capitals, respectively.  Ceded to Rhode Island in 1746 and is now part of Bristol County, Rhode Island.
: Dartmouth, Massachusetts Dartmouth, incorporated 1664.  Dartmouth was the site of a significant massacre by the Indian forces during King Philip's War.  It was also the location of a surrender of a group of some 160 of Philip's forces who were later sold into slavery.cite web   last = Nason   first = Elias   coauthor = George G. Varney   title = Dartmouth Massachusetts, 1890   work = Massachusetts Gazetteer   date = 1890   url = http://capecodhistory.us/Mass1890/Dartmouth1890.htm   accessdate = 2007-04-03
